  <!-- Architecture -->
  <section id="architektura">
    <h2>Architecture</h2>

    <pre><code>GitHub Projects (UI)  &lt;--&gt;  .edpa/ item files (Git)
       |                          |
  PM/BO operate            Versioned, auditable
       |                          |
  Issue Types (org)        EDPA engine (compute)
       |                          |
  Custom fields            Reports + Snapshots</code></pre>

    <h3>Data flow</h3>
    <pre><code>                    +---------------------------+
                    |    GitHub Projects (UI)    |
                    |  PM/BO manage the backlog  |
                    +---------------------------+
                         |              ^
           sync pull     |              |     sync push
         (cron 15min)    v              |   (push trigger)
                    +---------------------------+
                    |  .edpa/ item files (Git)   |
                    |  Source of truth           |
                    +---------------------------+
                              |
                    +---------+---------+
                    |                   |
              +----------+       +----------+
              |  Engine  |       |  Backlog |
              | (compute)|       |  CLI     |
              +----------+       +----------+
                    |                   |
              +----------+       +----------+
              | Reports  |       |  WSJF    |
              | Snapshots|       |  Tree    |
              | Timesheet|       |  Validate|
              +----------+       +----------+</code></pre>

    <h3>Evidence detection</h3>
    <div class="card">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Signal</th><th style="text-align:right">Weight</th><th>Derived role (display)</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>GitHub issue assignee</td><td style="text-align:right">4.00</td><td>owner</td></tr>
          <tr><td>PR author referencing item</td><td style="text-align:right">3.40</td><td>key</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Commit author with S-XXX/F-XXX</td><td style="text-align:right">2.78</td><td>reviewer</td></tr>
          <tr><td>PR reviewer</td><td style="text-align:right">2.25</td><td>reviewer</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Issue/PR comment</td><td style="text-align:right">1.14</td><td>consulted</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>/contribute @person weight:X</code></td><td style="text-align:right">explicit</td><td>key (default)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>Signals <strong>aggregate additively</strong> into contribution_score per (person, item), then normalize per-item: <code>cw = score / Σ_persons score</code> (Σ across persons = 1.0). Role label is derived from dominant signal type for display only, not stored.</p>

    <h3>EDPA calculation — gated</h3>
    <p>For each person in an iteration:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Detect evidence signals per (person, item) via <code>detect_contributors.py</code></li>
      <li>Per-item normalization: <code>cw_i = contribution_score_i / Σ_persons contribution_score</code> (Σ cw per item = 1.0)</li>
      <li>Stories at <code>status: Done</code> + Feature/Epic/Initiative gate transitions from git history: <code>score = JS × cw</code> (gates: <code>JS × gate_weight × cw</code>)</li>
      <li>Per person: <code>ratio_i = score_i / Σ scores</code></li>
      <li>Derived hours: <code>hours_i = ratio_i × capacity</code></li>
    </ol>
    <div class="note"><strong>Invariants:</strong> <code>Σ hours = capacity</code> per person AND <code>Σ cw = 1.0</code> per item — always, by construction.</div>
  </section>

  <!-- Troubleshooting -->
  <section id="troubleshooting">
    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

    <h3>gh auth — missing scopes</h3>
    <pre><code>ERROR: insufficient scopes for organization query</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong></p>
    <pre><code>gh auth refresh -s repo,project,read:project,admin:org
gh auth status  # verify</code></pre>

    <h3>Issue Types — "Not Found" during setup</h3>
    <pre><code>ERROR: Organization not found or insufficient permissions</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Verify you are a member of the organization with admin rights</li>
      <li>Issue Types require org-level access (not a personal account)</li>
      <li><code>gh auth refresh -s admin:org</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Backlog validate — errors</h3>
    <pre><code>ERROR: S-200 references non-existent feature F-999</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> verify that every <code>feature:</code> reference in stories points to an existing feature.</p>
    <pre><code>WARNING: S-200 Job Size out of range (JS=120, range=1..100)</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> Job Size is outside the modified Fibonacci scale (1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 20, 40, 100). If the item really is that large, consider breaking it down &mdash; but fixed per-level caps no longer apply, granularity is the team's responsibility during refinement.</p>

    <h3>EDPA engine — invariant failure</h3>
    <pre><code>INVARIANT FAILURE -- check results
All invariants passed: NO</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Possible causes:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Person has no evidence (not assignee, no commits)</li>
      <li>All CW values are 0</li>
      <li>Capacity is 0</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> verify every person has at least one assigned work item, commits/PRs reference the correct item IDs, capacities &gt; 0 in <code>.edpa/config/people.yaml</code>.</p>

    <h3>Sync — conflicts</h3>
    <pre><code>CONFLICT: S-200 modified in both Git and Projects</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong></p>
    <p><strong>Claude Code (recommended):</strong></p>
    <pre><code>/edpa sync diff       # show diffs
/edpa sync push       # after resolving the conflict</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Manual CLI:</strong></p>
    <pre><code># Show conflicts
python3 .claude/edpa/scripts/sync.py conflicts

# Diff
python3 .claude/edpa/scripts/sync.py diff</code></pre>
    <p>Resolve manually in the relevant item file in <code>.edpa/</code>, then:</p>
    <pre><code>python3 .claude/edpa/scripts/sync.py push</code></pre>

    <h3>Sync — loop prevention</h3>
    <p>The <code>edpa-sync-git-to-projects.yml</code> workflow contains:</p>
    <pre><code>if: github.actor != 'github-actions[bot]'</code></pre>
    <p>This prevents an infinite loop: push &rarr; sync &rarr; push &rarr; sync...</p>

    <h3>GitHub Project — missing custom fields</h3>
    <pre><code>ERROR: Field "Job Size" not found on project</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> re-run <code>project_setup.py</code>, or manually: Settings &rarr; Custom fields &rarr; Add field.</p>

    <h3>Branch naming CI failure</h3>
    <pre><code>Branch name does not follow EDPA convention.
Required format: &#123;type&#125;/&#123;item-id&#125;-&#123;description&#125;</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> use the format <code>feature/S-200-omop-parser</code>. Types: <code>feature</code>, <code>defect</code>, <code>hotfix</code>, <code>chore</code>. <code>main</code>, <code>develop</code>, <code>release/*</code> are exceptions.</p>

    <h3>MAD too high (&gt; 0.10)</h3>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong></p>
    <ol>
      <li>Analyze records with the largest <code>abs(predicted_cw - confirmed_cw)</code> per (person, item)</li>
      <li>Group by dominant signal type (assignee / pr_author / commit_author / pr_reviewer / issue_comment)</li>
      <li>If a strategic role (PM / BO / Arch) is systematically under-credited, the calibrator increases <code>signals.issue_comment</code> or <code>signals.pr_reviewer</code> weight</li>
      <li>Run <code>python3 .claude/edpa/scripts/calibrate_signals.py --apply</code> to re-baseline against current ground truth</li>
      <li>Re-run engine, verify invariants + new MAD</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Iteration close — "config not found"</h3>
    <pre><code>ERROR: .edpa/config/people.yaml not found. Run EDPA setup first.</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Fix:</strong></p>
    <pre><code># /edpa setup generates .edpa/config/people.yaml automatically
# /edpa setup generates .edpa/config/heuristics.yaml automatically
# /edpa setup generates .edpa/config/project.yaml automatically</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- Glossary -->
  <section id="slovnicek">
    <h2>Glossary</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Term</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>PI</strong></td><td>Planning Interval (10 weeks = 4 delivery + 1 IP iteration)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>IP</strong></td><td>Innovation &amp; Planning (the last iteration of a PI)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>JS</strong></td><td>Job Size — relative work size (Fibonacci)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>BV</strong></td><td>Business Value</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>TC</strong></td><td>Time Criticality</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>RR&amp;OE</strong></td><td>Risk Reduction &amp; Opportunity Enablement</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>WSJF</strong></td><td>Weighted Shortest Job First = (BV+TC+RR&amp;OE)/JS</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>cw</strong></td><td>Contribution Weight — per-item share (Σ across persons = 1.0)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>contribution_score</strong></td><td>Raw sum of signal weights (audit input)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>signals[]</strong></td><td>Audit trail: type/ref/weight/detected_at per signal</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>MAD</strong></td><td>Mean Absolute Deviation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Evidence</strong></td><td>Proof of work (commit, PR, assignee, comment)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Ground truth</strong></td><td>Team-confirmed reality (used for calibration)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

